WEBVTT

00:00.367 --> 00:01.602
...and then I kissed him,

00:01.602 --> 00:03.937
and I think
I caught him off guard,

00:03.937 --> 00:05.539
because he said
I caught him off guard,

00:05.539 --> 00:07.608
and then he wouldn't talk to me
for the rest of the day.

00:07.608 --> 00:08.742
Wow!

00:08.742 --> 00:10.577
Your first bad boy.

00:10.577 --> 00:12.346
So, you gonna go
full Russian now

00:12.346 --> 00:14.615
and start rockin' high heels
and a floor-length fur

00:14.615 --> 00:17.050
and drinking
lots of soup?

00:17.050 --> 00:19.586
Do Russian women
drink lots of soup?

00:19.586 --> 00:21.121
I dunno.
I've never been anywhere.

00:21.121 --> 00:23.757
Well, I don't think
we're gonna date or anything.

00:23.757 --> 00:25.459
I mean, it was hot,

00:25.459 --> 00:27.527
but I don't really think
I'm Vlad's type.

00:27.527 --> 00:29.596
Yeah.
You're way too vanilla.

00:29.596 --> 00:32.132
He probably made out
with some club skank after

00:32.132 --> 00:35.469
just to wash the taste
of nerd-mom out of his mouth.

00:35.469 --> 00:39.640
Say what you will but
"Nerd Mom" is doing a-okay.

00:39.640 --> 00:42.075
Check the, uh, scoreboard.

00:42.075 --> 00:44.077
Wes? Vlad?

00:44.077 --> 00:45.379
Two guys.

00:45.379 --> 00:46.446
Yeah!

00:46.446 --> 00:48.282
Scoreboard's a'two!

00:48.282 --> 00:50.150
That's a two-ski!

00:50.150 --> 00:51.985
A deuce-a-rooni.

00:54.121 --> 00:55.889
Are you making fun
of yourself right now?

00:55.889 --> 00:57.090
No.

00:57.090 --> 00:59.226
♪♪

00:59.226 --> 01:02.629
♪ Keep giving me hope
for a better day ♪

01:02.629 --> 01:05.799
♪ Keep giving me love
to find a way ♪

01:05.799 --> 01:09.136
♪ Through this heaviness
I feel ♪

01:09.136 --> 01:15.442
♪ I just need someone to say
everything's okay ♪

01:15.442 --> 01:17.311
♪ Everything's okay ♪

01:17.311 --> 01:19.146
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:19.146 --> 01:20.781
[ Alarm ringing ]

01:20.781 --> 01:22.583
[ Sighs ]

01:25.652 --> 01:27.321
Hey...good morning.

01:27.321 --> 01:28.689
Hey.
'Sup.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.824
Mm. Hey.
Paige, could you...

01:30.824 --> 01:32.592
Um...

01:32.592 --> 01:34.795
First of all, you're great.
[ Chuckles ]

01:34.795 --> 01:36.663
Second, could you
get out of here real quick?

01:36.663 --> 01:38.098
What?
Lena and I agreed

01:38.098 --> 01:39.833
that we're not supposed
to have overnight guests

01:39.833 --> 01:41.034
in the main house...

01:41.034 --> 01:42.703
Dear God. You people.
I know.

01:42.703 --> 01:44.271
I know, I know,
but you can go out,

01:44.271 --> 01:45.772
ring the doorbell,
come right back in.

01:45.772 --> 01:46.940
Cool offer,

01:46.940 --> 01:48.442
but I think
I'm gonna head home.

01:48.442 --> 01:50.677
Okay. But for the record,

01:50.677 --> 01:52.713
that's why I suggested
we stay at your place.

01:54.014 --> 01:56.850
Yeah, well, I like
to keep my place clean.

01:56.850 --> 01:58.285
And you're messy.

01:58.285 --> 01:59.686
No, I'm not!

01:59.686 --> 02:00.854
No, I have a credit
at the Container Store.

02:00.854 --> 02:01.855
They know me there.

02:01.855 --> 02:03.790
You're not literally messy.

02:03.790 --> 02:06.994
I mean, you and your ex-wife
and the musical beds?

02:06.994 --> 02:08.061
It's a lot.

02:08.061 --> 02:09.363
Oh, come on.
It's totally --

02:09.363 --> 02:10.197
[ Knocking on door ]

02:10.197 --> 02:11.198
Martin?

02:11.198 --> 02:13.333
Oh crap. We're dead.
Hide!

02:13.333 --> 02:15.202
No. We're 40.

02:15.202 --> 02:16.570
Eh, Um...

02:16.570 --> 02:18.305
Just a second.

02:18.305 --> 02:21.541
Dad? Can I use your bathroom?
Mason's taking forever.

02:21.541 --> 02:22.976
Let's give Daddy
a second.

02:22.976 --> 02:25.212
I think his special
lady friend is in there.

02:25.212 --> 02:26.546
[ Chuckles ] You see?

02:26.546 --> 02:29.516
Huh? You see what
I'm up against here?

02:29.516 --> 02:31.151
Your place, please.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.687
-How about tonight?
-I'm in.

02:33.687 --> 02:36.890
♪♪

02:36.890 --> 02:38.158
I'm not doing that.

02:38.158 --> 02:40.594
No, totally,
I didn't expect you to.

02:40.594 --> 02:43.163
So, uh, seriously...

02:43.163 --> 02:45.165
[ Exhales sharply ]
What -- what's the plan?

02:45.165 --> 02:45.999
Oh.

02:45.999 --> 02:47.401
That door? Okay.

02:47.401 --> 02:48.568
Good. Uh...

02:48.568 --> 02:49.403
Oh...

02:49.403 --> 02:51.338
[ Door closes ]

02:51.338 --> 02:52.506
[ Sighs ]

02:54.241 --> 02:57.677
Look, we fell asleep last night
watching TV, okay?

02:57.677 --> 02:59.913
I'm an adult,
I'm not gonna apologize --

02:59.913 --> 03:01.748
but obviously,
I'm incredibly sorry.

03:01.748 --> 03:03.383
Well, since we're
ignoring all the rules

03:03.383 --> 03:04.851
that we mutually agreed upon,

03:04.851 --> 03:06.920
maybe Vlad and I can work
inside the house today.

03:06.920 --> 03:08.855
There's virtually no room to
spread out in the garage,

03:08.855 --> 03:10.090
and we need
a real work surface.

03:10.090 --> 03:12.092
Okay, yeah,
I'm open to that,

03:12.092 --> 03:14.428
but will you stay
with the kids tonight,

03:14.428 --> 03:16.963
while I go to Paige's house
for some privacy?

03:16.963 --> 03:18.598
Oh, yeah, privacy.

03:18.598 --> 03:21.268
That thing that dads love
but moms never experience.

03:21.268 --> 03:22.803
Don't widen this.

03:22.803 --> 03:25.772
Fine, I'll watch your kids.
But we're working inside.

03:25.772 --> 03:27.274
[ Knocking on door ]

03:27.274 --> 03:30.610
♪♪

03:30.610 --> 03:32.145
Hey, Nathaniel.

03:32.145 --> 03:35.115
Morning, Mr. Dubs.
Is Mason Bourne on the premises?

03:35.115 --> 03:37.117
Checking to see if he wants
to walk to school together.

03:37.117 --> 03:37.984
Um...

03:41.721 --> 03:43.623
Sorry, bud. He...

03:43.623 --> 03:44.458
He already left.

03:44.458 --> 03:45.725
No problemo.

03:45.725 --> 03:48.261
However, I would love
to reconnect.

03:48.261 --> 03:50.263
Could you let him know
I came calling?

03:50.263 --> 03:52.132
[ Clicks tongue ]
Will do.

03:52.132 --> 03:53.500
Cool.
Cool.

03:54.801 --> 03:56.002
Bye.

03:58.438 --> 04:00.640
What are you doing, treating
Nathaniel like that, huh?

04:00.640 --> 04:01.842
Shame on you!

04:01.842 --> 04:03.610
You guys went
to pre-school together.

04:03.610 --> 04:06.146
Exactly!
And he won't let go.

04:06.146 --> 04:08.815
We have nothing
in common anymore, okay?

04:08.815 --> 04:10.984
I've been in a relationship,
for God's sake.

04:10.984 --> 04:14.454
[ Chuckles ]
And this kid
still plays with Legos.

04:14.454 --> 04:16.323
May I have him?

04:16.323 --> 04:18.625
Go get your bag. Go.
[ Sighs ]

04:18.625 --> 04:22.129
Mason, Nathaniel,
he looks up to you.

04:22.129 --> 04:23.997
He looks up to everybody!

04:23.997 --> 04:24.998
He's tiny!

04:24.998 --> 04:26.867
And besides, I'm busy.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.201
There's this girl --

04:28.201 --> 04:30.437
Hazel.
Always Hazel.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.304
Someone else.

04:32.272 --> 04:33.440
Whoa!

04:33.440 --> 04:36.610
The spell has been broken!

04:36.610 --> 04:38.678
My man!
Who's the lucky lady?

04:38.678 --> 04:39.846
Her name's Bronwyn.

04:39.846 --> 04:41.047
What?!

04:41.047 --> 04:43.350
Bronwyn?
You like Bronwyn?

04:43.350 --> 04:44.851
That's hilarious.

04:44.851 --> 04:46.386
Why is it hilarious?

04:46.386 --> 04:47.954
She's, like, the most
pretentious girl in our school.

04:47.954 --> 04:49.656
Shut up, Mae.

04:49.656 --> 04:51.858
You're just mad that she got
voted lit mag editor over you.

04:51.858 --> 04:53.360
That's only because
her dad co-wrote

04:53.360 --> 04:54.961
"Diary of
an Underpants Weirdo."

04:54.961 --> 04:57.030
He did?
I love those books!

04:57.030 --> 04:59.166
Wow, she must be,
like, super talented.

04:59.166 --> 05:00.467
Just 'cause her dad's
a good writer

05:00.467 --> 05:01.468
doesn't mean she is.

05:01.468 --> 05:02.702
I'm way more talented.

05:02.702 --> 05:04.070
Hmm.

05:04.070 --> 05:06.873
Lena?
Care to weigh in? Hmm?

05:06.873 --> 05:08.208
Who's a better writer,

05:08.208 --> 05:10.043
the Underpants daughter
or our girl?

05:10.043 --> 05:12.312
[ Door closes ]
I'm sure
they're both gifted.

05:12.312 --> 05:15.348
You're not even listening!
Just side with me.

05:15.348 --> 05:18.685
I'm sorry!
I would need to read both first.

05:18.685 --> 05:20.187
No OJ?

05:20.187 --> 05:22.055
Oh, I'll pick some up
after I drop the kids.

05:22.055 --> 05:23.323
Thanks, honey.

05:23.323 --> 05:24.824
You're welcome, honey.
[ Smooching ]

05:24.824 --> 05:25.859
[ Smooches ]

05:25.859 --> 05:27.160
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.160 --> 05:28.895
Oh, man, Paige was right.

05:28.895 --> 05:30.397
We are messy.

05:30.397 --> 05:31.998
We are messy as hell.

05:31.998 --> 05:33.266
Lena: She said that?

05:33.266 --> 05:35.235
Guys, in the car.
Milo, let's go!

05:35.235 --> 05:37.571
Hey, I'm warning you.

05:37.571 --> 05:39.906
If Bronwyn steps foot
in this house,

05:39.906 --> 05:41.408
there's gonna be hell to pay.

05:41.408 --> 05:43.176
[ Chuckles ]
Whatever, Mae.

05:44.511 --> 05:45.912
[ Sighs ]
Sorry about all that.

05:45.912 --> 05:47.047
What a madhouse.

05:47.047 --> 05:48.114
Hmm.

05:48.114 --> 05:49.683
Should we get started?
Sure.

05:51.084 --> 05:54.421
First off, um,
what are we?

05:54.421 --> 05:56.256
[ Laughs ]

05:56.256 --> 05:57.624
No, seriously.

05:59.392 --> 06:00.927
Us.
What -- what are we?

06:00.927 --> 06:03.863
Do you mean what are we...
romantically?

06:03.863 --> 06:06.466
Yeah.

06:06.466 --> 06:07.801
Nothing?

06:07.801 --> 06:09.436
Ahh. Okay.

06:09.436 --> 06:11.037
But, uh...

06:11.037 --> 06:12.372
What, though?

06:12.372 --> 06:13.240
What, what?

06:14.708 --> 06:15.709
The kiss?

06:15.709 --> 06:17.310
Yeah.

06:17.310 --> 06:21.448
I was just trying to prove
to you that I was over Martin...

06:21.448 --> 06:23.083
I see.

06:23.083 --> 06:24.484
I mean,
I figured it was okay

06:24.484 --> 06:26.753
because you kissed me first
to make a point.

06:26.753 --> 06:29.756
And I didn't think
you were attracted to me.

06:29.756 --> 06:31.057
I wasn't.

06:31.057 --> 06:32.626
And I thought
you were deeply boring.

06:32.626 --> 06:35.962
Like a piece
of printer paper.

06:37.330 --> 06:41.301
But then,
the kiss was, uh...

06:41.301 --> 06:42.669
[ Clears throat ]

06:42.669 --> 06:45.171
[ Cellphone clicking ]
I knew the word.

06:45.171 --> 06:48.575
It was...

06:48.575 --> 06:50.410
Ah, volcanic.

06:50.410 --> 06:51.645
Really?
Yeah.

06:51.645 --> 06:53.446
Wow.

06:53.446 --> 06:54.514
I mean, I...

06:54.514 --> 06:56.149
I don't know what to say.

06:56.149 --> 06:59.819
Well, is it possible
that we're at the point

06:59.819 --> 07:02.322
where we don't
need words anymore?

07:04.090 --> 07:06.326
I don't think so?

07:06.326 --> 07:07.961
Um...

07:07.961 --> 07:09.996
Maybe we should just
put a pin in this discussion

07:09.996 --> 07:12.766
and concentrate on the boards
for today's meeting.

07:12.766 --> 07:15.435
Absolutely. Very, uh...

07:15.435 --> 07:18.038
Super smart.

07:18.038 --> 07:20.507
So, um, I mocked this up --

07:20.507 --> 07:21.708
I like this color.

07:21.708 --> 07:23.777
What -- What is the soap
you're using?

07:23.777 --> 07:24.678
It's so good.

07:24.678 --> 07:26.112
It's scentless.

07:26.112 --> 07:27.047
I'm allergic to scent.

07:27.047 --> 07:30.016
It's...unscented.

07:30.016 --> 07:33.853
So what I'm smelling is...

07:33.853 --> 07:37.324
is just your flesh, huh?

07:37.324 --> 07:38.458
Mm-hmm.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.493
[ Clicks tongue ]
So good.

07:45.465 --> 07:46.066
[ School bell rings ]

07:46.066 --> 07:47.400
Hey, Bronwyn.

07:47.400 --> 07:50.303
Um, I was just wondering
if you could help me

07:50.303 --> 07:52.038
with my short story.

07:52.038 --> 07:53.907
Since you're such
a great writer and all...

07:53.907 --> 07:55.075
Oh, thanks.

07:55.075 --> 07:56.643
It's just in my DNA.

07:56.643 --> 07:57.877
I would share it
with you if I could.

07:57.877 --> 07:59.045
Or would I...?

07:59.045 --> 08:01.214
[ Laughs loudly ]

08:01.214 --> 08:03.216
Barf.

08:03.216 --> 08:06.386
So, that's what your brother
looks like flirting, huh?

08:06.386 --> 08:08.555
Yeah.

08:08.555 --> 08:11.224
Even grosser
than I thought.

08:11.224 --> 08:13.760
I know I'll probably never
co-author anything,

08:13.760 --> 08:16.262
but, you know, if you could
just take a look

08:16.262 --> 08:17.530
and tell me what you think.

08:17.530 --> 08:18.698
Like a mentor?

08:18.698 --> 08:20.567
Or a...muse?

08:20.567 --> 08:21.901
Interesting.

08:21.901 --> 08:23.236
Mason told me
he couldn't hang out today

08:23.236 --> 08:24.671
'cause he had study hall,

08:24.671 --> 08:27.240
but it would appear
he just has...hall.

08:27.240 --> 08:28.842
Open your eyes, kid.

08:28.842 --> 08:30.744
You're getting big-timed.

08:30.744 --> 08:33.012
It's so hard for me to be
creative at school.

08:33.012 --> 08:35.682
You know, I just...
I don't feel fertile here.

08:35.682 --> 08:38.118
Okay then, your place.
After school.

08:38.118 --> 08:40.353
Cool! Coo-- Cool.

08:40.353 --> 08:43.757
He's doing it!
He's actually inviting her over.

08:43.757 --> 08:45.859
Instead of me?!

08:45.859 --> 08:47.060
Okay,
I am almost on the verge

08:47.060 --> 08:49.262
of maybe blocking him
on Xbox.

08:49.262 --> 08:53.366
Fine, I won't, just in case
he tries to message me.

08:53.366 --> 08:54.567
Please don't tell him
I said that.

08:54.567 --> 08:55.735
Seriously,
I'll be your slave.

08:57.437 --> 09:00.240
Hey, Nathaniel,
got any plans tonight?

09:01.207 --> 09:02.375
You know I don't.

09:05.311 --> 09:06.913
Maya: So he went
soft on you?

09:06.913 --> 09:08.948
This is the whole problem
with bad boys.

09:08.948 --> 09:10.884
I mean, you -- you
want them to get nicer,

09:10.884 --> 09:12.419
and then the second
that they warm up,

09:12.419 --> 09:14.421
it's game over.
Oh, no.

09:14.421 --> 09:16.723
You're not taking dating advice
from this woman, are you?

09:16.723 --> 09:19.225
Gene,
go get us more water.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.327
Lemme guess. Tap?

09:21.327 --> 09:24.097
I did not
see this coming.

09:24.097 --> 09:27.066
Am I, like,
a heartbreaker?

09:27.066 --> 09:29.736
Do I, like, ruin men?

09:30.804 --> 09:32.071
Does that guy want me?

09:34.641 --> 09:36.075
Possibly.

09:36.075 --> 09:38.645
I can't get into another
relationship right now.

09:38.645 --> 09:40.747
I have options to explore.

09:40.747 --> 09:43.116
That guy. Wes.

09:43.116 --> 09:45.185
Wes' girlfriend might
wanna do stuff with me...

09:45.185 --> 09:47.520
You're not worried
at all about torpedoing

09:47.520 --> 09:49.522
this brand-new business
partnership with Vlad?

09:49.522 --> 09:50.924
Why would it?

09:50.924 --> 09:51.758
You think he's not
gonna wanna work with me

09:51.758 --> 09:53.293
if I don't reciprocate?

09:53.293 --> 09:54.194
I don't know.

09:54.194 --> 09:55.361
Guy caught feelings.

09:55.361 --> 09:57.030
Who knows how
he's gonna react?

09:57.030 --> 09:58.364
Me, I'd burn it down.

09:58.364 --> 09:59.632
I'd burn down everything
you ever loved.

09:59.632 --> 10:01.201
[ Scoffs ]
Don't be silly, Gene!

10:01.201 --> 10:02.869
You've never
loved anything.

10:02.869 --> 10:05.438
Tell that to the movie
"Dunkirk."

10:06.639 --> 10:08.975
I don't think Vlad would be
anything but professional.

10:08.975 --> 10:10.510
I'll just tell him.

10:12.679 --> 10:14.113
After our meeting.

10:14.113 --> 10:20.620
♪♪

10:20.620 --> 10:22.355
Oh, honey, I'm home.

10:22.355 --> 10:23.723
[ Laughs ]
Come on in.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.528
Wow!

10:28.528 --> 10:30.563
So, this is you?

10:30.563 --> 10:32.031
This is me.

10:32.031 --> 10:33.233
Mm.

10:34.567 --> 10:36.536
Oh...

10:36.536 --> 10:37.737
There it is.
Hmm.

10:37.737 --> 10:40.206
The quiet.
Oh, I missed you, quiet.

10:40.206 --> 10:42.075
It's nice, right?
Oh, my God, it's so nice.

10:42.075 --> 10:43.309
[ Both chuckle ]

10:43.309 --> 10:44.677
I brought you some wine.
Thank you.

10:44.677 --> 10:45.879
[ Cellphone dings ]

10:45.879 --> 10:48.314
My ex is dropping off
my son soon.

10:48.314 --> 10:49.883
Oh, so I get
to meet your ex.

10:49.883 --> 10:51.251
Uh, no.

10:51.251 --> 10:53.219
He drops him off.
He doesn't come in.

10:54.754 --> 10:56.823
Oh, you -- you -- you guys --
you don't speak?

10:56.823 --> 10:58.391
We do sometimes,

10:58.391 --> 11:00.927
just not ever once
in the past 12 years.
Oh.

11:00.927 --> 11:02.762
Sometimes,
if I'm feeling nostalgic,

11:02.762 --> 11:04.330
I give him the finger
through the window.

11:04.330 --> 11:06.666
Mm. [ Chuckles ]
Good one.

11:06.666 --> 11:07.767
[ Door opens ]

11:07.767 --> 11:09.235
Hey, Mom.

11:09.235 --> 11:10.737
Cool Hand Luke!

11:10.737 --> 11:12.405
Ah! Hey, buddy!

11:12.405 --> 11:13.673
Did you have a good day
at sch--

11:13.673 --> 11:15.508
Whoa!

11:15.508 --> 11:16.709
He has a tattoo.

11:16.709 --> 11:19.078
-Yeah, it's his body.
-Is it?

11:19.078 --> 11:20.713
Dad said he needs me
on Thanksgiving this year.

11:20.713 --> 11:22.549
What?
He had you last year.

11:22.549 --> 11:24.017
He said you can have
my birthday.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.685
Yeah! I'll bet he did.

11:25.685 --> 11:27.453
Tell him that he still has
to split the party with me.

11:27.453 --> 11:29.088
I will.

11:29.088 --> 11:30.056
Love you.

11:30.056 --> 11:31.624
Love you!

11:31.624 --> 11:33.059
Wow.

11:33.059 --> 11:35.428
So he's, like,
self-sufficient.

11:35.428 --> 11:38.064
You say that like
it's a bad thing --

11:38.064 --> 11:40.366
He just seems so mature.

11:40.366 --> 11:41.367
Thank you.

11:41.367 --> 11:43.236
Hardened.

11:43.236 --> 11:44.771
Like a war vet...

11:44.771 --> 11:46.272
Luke's doing great.

11:46.272 --> 11:47.273
Don't worry.

11:47.273 --> 11:48.274
Yeah?

11:48.274 --> 11:50.376
What about you, hmm?

11:50.376 --> 11:52.712
You gonna spend Thanksgiving
all by yourself again?

11:52.712 --> 11:54.280
I eat with friends.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.448
And we get loaded.

11:55.448 --> 11:57.951
We go out
for Brazilian buffet.

11:57.951 --> 11:58.952
It's pretty awesome.

11:58.952 --> 12:00.453
Yeah.

12:00.453 --> 12:02.956
Look, my divorce
works for me.

12:02.956 --> 12:04.457
I get the best
of both worlds.

12:04.457 --> 12:06.593
I get one-on-one time
with my son,

12:06.593 --> 12:07.760
and then when
he's with his dad,

12:07.760 --> 12:09.729
I get plenty of time
for myself.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.998
Hey, Mom, is it cool if I
sleep over at Matty's tonight?

12:11.998 --> 12:15.234
You've been gone all week!
She barely got to see you!

12:15.234 --> 12:16.970
It's fine.

12:16.970 --> 12:19.672
Arcade Fire, this weekend --
Are we still on?

12:19.672 --> 12:21.741
-Still on.
-[ Chuckles ]

12:21.741 --> 12:23.810
Excuse me, mister.
Are you forgetting something?

12:23.810 --> 12:25.311
Oh, right.

12:25.311 --> 12:27.847
♪♪

12:27.847 --> 12:29.816
-Here's your check.
-Thank you.

12:29.816 --> 12:30.984
Oh, now, wait a minute.

12:30.984 --> 12:32.919
Are we chargin' this kid
rent?

12:32.919 --> 12:34.754
Hmm? Because
he's barely here.

12:34.754 --> 12:38.157
It's child support.
From my dad.

12:38.157 --> 12:39.525
Oh.

12:39.525 --> 12:45.298
♪♪

12:45.298 --> 12:51.004
♪♪

12:51.004 --> 12:58.511
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

12:58.511 --> 12:59.512
Oh, crap.

12:59.512 --> 13:00.847
[ Cellphone clicks ]

13:00.847 --> 13:03.182
Martin? Everything okay?

13:03.182 --> 13:05.018
Martin: Yeah, yeah,
everything's okay.

13:05.018 --> 13:06.686
I, uh...

13:06.686 --> 13:08.988
I just wanted
to hear your voice.

13:08.988 --> 13:10.990
I-I mean,
I just wanted to say...

13:10.990 --> 13:12.025
[ Clears throat ]

13:12.025 --> 13:13.826
You're a good mom.

13:13.826 --> 13:15.228
I...I just --

13:15.228 --> 13:17.296
I like the kind of mom
you are, is all.

13:17.296 --> 13:18.698
So, thank you.

13:18.698 --> 13:20.466
For being that way.

13:20.466 --> 13:21.567
Are you dying?

13:21.567 --> 13:23.369
No, not yet.
[ Chuckles ]

13:23.369 --> 13:25.038
But I did come home early.

13:25.038 --> 13:30.209
And, uh, I'm not gonna be going
out tonight after all, so...

13:30.209 --> 13:31.644
I'll see you
when you get here?

13:31.644 --> 13:32.979
Uh, yeah, I'm just --

13:32.979 --> 13:34.347
I'm just
walking into a meeting,

13:34.347 --> 13:35.915
and I'll be home
right after.

13:35.915 --> 13:37.016
Ah, cool, cool.

13:37.016 --> 13:38.384
Cool. Yeah, I'm, uh...

13:38.384 --> 13:39.585
I'm here.

13:39.585 --> 13:40.920
Hey, uh,
if you're interested,

13:40.920 --> 13:42.989
there's some chili
in the freezer.

13:42.989 --> 13:46.092
Thanks, yeah.

13:46.092 --> 13:47.326
I'm interested.

13:49.696 --> 13:52.565
I feel the story inside me,
clawing to get out,

13:52.565 --> 13:55.735
but I don't know how
to open the door for it.

13:55.735 --> 13:57.437
Yeah.

13:57.437 --> 13:59.906
Maybe it shouldn't
just be about a hill.

13:59.906 --> 14:02.408
What if you try putting
some people in there?

14:02.408 --> 14:05.078
Okay.

14:05.078 --> 14:06.345
See? It's already
getting better.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.181
You're amazing.

14:08.181 --> 14:10.516
Are you guys
falling in love?

14:10.516 --> 14:12.919
Dude, don't you have something
you want to go do?

14:12.919 --> 14:15.088
Yes, I'm doing it.

14:15.088 --> 14:16.456
Just pretend
he's not here.

14:16.456 --> 14:19.192
[ Shrill laughter in distance ]

14:20.560 --> 14:23.062
Is that your
sister laughing?

14:23.062 --> 14:25.064
That's not my sister.

14:25.064 --> 14:27.033
[ Laughing continues ]

14:27.033 --> 14:29.435
[ Laughs ]

14:29.435 --> 14:31.104
You're pathetic, Mae.

14:31.104 --> 14:32.605
You seriously
invited him over here

14:32.605 --> 14:34.407
just to get back at me
for Bronwyn?

14:34.407 --> 14:36.109
We're hanging out, Mason.
Ever heard of it?

14:36.109 --> 14:37.910
You should
try it sometime.

14:37.910 --> 14:38.878
With me.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.313
You're obsessed with me.

14:40.313 --> 14:42.315
Your ego
is out of control.

14:42.315 --> 14:44.417
Oh, then he and Bronwyn
are perfect for each other.

14:44.417 --> 14:45.752
What did I do?

14:45.752 --> 14:47.286
It's more of what
you didn't do,

14:47.286 --> 14:48.955
which is co-author
"Diary of an Underpants Weirdo"!

14:48.955 --> 14:50.456
It's inspired by me!

14:50.456 --> 14:52.258
[ Book thuds ]
Whoops!

14:52.258 --> 14:54.427
Just dropped the instructions
for my 500-piece

14:54.427 --> 14:57.063
special-anniversary edition
Justice League set.

14:57.063 --> 14:59.265
[ Sighs ] Milo, I'm never
going to play Lego with you.

14:59.265 --> 15:00.266
Just give it up.

15:00.266 --> 15:02.135
Same, dude! Same!

15:02.135 --> 15:04.137
All right,
you're ridiculous, huh?

15:04.137 --> 15:06.172
Let's just put that
as a fact.
I'm being ridiculous?

15:06.172 --> 15:08.508
Yes!
You invited him over here just
because I invited her over here.

15:08.508 --> 15:10.076
Can we just agree that everybody
here is being ridiculous?
You invited Bronwyn, okay?

15:10.076 --> 15:12.445
Why can't you just...
I'm not the one who's --

15:12.445 --> 15:13.946
...because it's classic
and traditional, okay?
I'm the one who's not getting --

15:16.449 --> 15:18.518
[ Echoing ]
Hellew, hellew?

15:18.518 --> 15:19.952
There!
You heard it?

15:19.952 --> 15:21.521
Hellew --

15:21.521 --> 15:22.789
There's an echo.

15:22.789 --> 15:23.923
Hello.

15:23.923 --> 15:27.326
No, no.
It's hellew, hellew --

15:27.326 --> 15:29.428
Okay, wait just a second.
If you stop doing it --

15:29.428 --> 15:31.831
If I stop doing it,
you won't hear it.

15:31.831 --> 15:33.800
Right!

15:33.800 --> 15:35.168
The client's always right.

15:36.502 --> 15:37.470
How about this.

15:37.470 --> 15:39.438
We bring in some textiles,

15:39.438 --> 15:41.808
all in keeping
with your Grecian motif.

15:41.808 --> 15:45.678
Maybe some key pattern rugs,
wall tapestries,

15:45.678 --> 15:49.682
silk window treatments,
all very regal, all very grand,

15:49.682 --> 15:52.518
all of which will absorb
the "hellews"...

15:52.518 --> 15:53.519
So cute.

15:56.322 --> 16:00.193
I'm sorry.
You're just...so cute.

16:00.193 --> 16:01.194
[ Chuckles ]

16:02.195 --> 16:04.530
I would also
love to incorporate

16:04.530 --> 16:06.299
some oversized
light fixtures

16:06.299 --> 16:09.802
just to accentuate
the grandeur of the space.

16:09.802 --> 16:12.538
She's just so cute, right?

16:12.538 --> 16:13.873
You know,
when I first met her,

16:13.873 --> 16:16.209
even the sound of her voice
was grating.

16:16.209 --> 16:18.644
But now, it's like...

16:18.644 --> 16:20.713
[ Sighs ]

16:20.713 --> 16:22.515
I just can't get enough.

16:22.515 --> 16:25.518
Vlad, this is not the image
that we want to project.

16:25.518 --> 16:26.919
What do you mean?

16:26.919 --> 16:30.590
A sexy couple that
makes houses and love?

16:30.590 --> 16:32.391
That's everybody's dream,
no?

16:32.391 --> 16:35.428
And maybe even possibly
a basic cable show.

16:37.230 --> 16:38.564
Look at her face, huh?

16:38.564 --> 16:40.066
She's in.

16:40.066 --> 16:42.034
♪♪

16:46.572 --> 16:48.074
[ Indistinct yelling ]

16:48.074 --> 16:49.408
One at a time.
One at a time.

16:49.408 --> 16:50.910
Mason --

16:50.910 --> 16:53.079
Listen to me!
It should matter when I yell!

16:53.079 --> 16:54.847
It should matter
when I yell!!

16:54.847 --> 16:56.883
How come none of you
are listening to me?!

16:56.883 --> 16:58.084
It should matter when --
Kids!

17:00.019 --> 17:01.754
Thank God you're home.

17:01.754 --> 17:03.422
Everyone take a deep breath.

17:03.422 --> 17:06.626
[ Everyone breathes deeply ]

17:07.627 --> 17:09.729
Okay, we're going to
sit down

17:09.729 --> 17:11.631
and discuss this calmly

17:11.631 --> 17:13.132
over some instant cocoa.

17:13.132 --> 17:14.634
Who wants marshmallows?

17:14.634 --> 17:15.801
Martin: [ Excitedly ]
Marshmallows, please!

17:16.936 --> 17:18.271
[ Coolly ]
Marshmallows.

17:20.106 --> 17:22.575
Lena:
Mae, I understand

17:22.575 --> 17:25.778
that you think
Bronwyn can be a lot,

17:25.778 --> 17:28.714
but here's the thing --
so can you.

17:28.714 --> 17:30.116
You two have
a lot in common.

17:30.116 --> 17:32.151
She and Mason
are gonna be hanging out,

17:32.151 --> 17:33.953
so try to be accepting.

17:33.953 --> 17:36.155
And, Mason, if you don't want
to hang out with Nathaniel,

17:36.155 --> 17:37.623
you got to be
up front with him.

17:37.623 --> 17:40.426
I don't want
to hang out with you.

17:40.426 --> 17:43.296
And, Nathaniel, you need
to stop being so thirsty.

17:43.296 --> 17:45.131
It's not helping
the cause, buddy.

17:45.131 --> 17:46.732
I'll be friends with you!

17:46.732 --> 17:49.802
Milo, what did your father
just say about being thirsty?

17:49.802 --> 17:53.906
Relationships only work
if both people are into them.

17:53.906 --> 17:55.308
Okay, If one isn't,

17:55.308 --> 17:57.343
it doesn't matter
how much the other one is.

17:57.343 --> 17:59.245
Where are you on Ninjago?

17:59.245 --> 18:01.080
I'd say I'm Ninjago-curious.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.849
We'll talk.
Yes!

18:03.849 --> 18:05.818
Well, there you go!
Everyone good?

18:05.818 --> 18:07.286
I guess.
Yeah.
Okay.

18:07.286 --> 18:09.188
-Okay, good. Meeting adjourned.
-Let's go.

18:10.189 --> 18:11.490
[ Sighs ]

18:11.490 --> 18:13.659
[ Martin chuckles ]

18:13.659 --> 18:15.861
[ Sighs ]
What are you gonna do?

18:15.861 --> 18:16.862
We're messy.

18:16.862 --> 18:18.164
Yeah.

18:18.164 --> 18:19.966
You know what?

18:19.966 --> 18:21.634
I don't mind.

18:21.634 --> 18:23.669
I'll take it over
the alternative any day.

18:23.669 --> 18:24.670
Really?

18:24.670 --> 18:26.339
Really.

18:26.339 --> 18:28.841
I think we're doing
something right, here.

18:28.841 --> 18:32.478
I can't imagine not being able
to see the kids every day

18:32.478 --> 18:36.515
or not being able to talk to you
just because we aren't...

18:36.515 --> 18:40.019
So are you saying you don't want
to sell the house anymore?

18:40.019 --> 18:43.022
I'm saying that
I can't imagine being divorced

18:43.022 --> 18:45.524
without you guys.

18:45.524 --> 18:46.726
[ Laughs ]

18:46.726 --> 18:48.394
[ Screams ]

18:48.394 --> 18:50.696
[ Both laugh ]

18:50.696 --> 18:52.531
Well, in that case...

18:52.531 --> 18:55.534
I'm gonna
fire our contractor.

18:55.534 --> 18:57.036
You are? Over what?

18:57.036 --> 18:58.371
He fell for me.

18:58.371 --> 18:59.872
Vlad? Stop it.

18:59.872 --> 19:01.540
He fell hard, bro.

19:01.540 --> 19:03.876
Wait. Y-You're kidding.

19:03.876 --> 19:04.877
You're kidding.

19:04.877 --> 19:06.312
You're not kidding?

19:06.312 --> 19:09.482
I'm a man-eater!
What can I say?

19:09.482 --> 19:12.318
What's gonna happen to your
joint business venture?

19:12.318 --> 19:16.655
Well, based on how
intoxicating my flesh is,

19:16.655 --> 19:18.024
I don't think
he can work with me.

19:18.024 --> 19:19.525
I mean,
I don't think he can be

19:19.525 --> 19:21.360
in the same vicinity as me.
Okay, wait a minute.

19:21.360 --> 19:23.329
So, I'm just gonna
have to go at it solo.

19:23.329 --> 19:25.197
Wait a minute.
I-I -- We --

19:25.197 --> 19:26.265
We need to get another
packet of hot chocolate
to talk about this.

19:26.265 --> 19:27.333
Come on.

19:28.401 --> 19:30.736
Did you guys kiss?
Oh, yeah.

19:30.736 --> 19:32.071
You did?!

19:32.071 --> 19:33.372
And he's not gonna
easily forget me.

19:33.372 --> 19:35.674
Ugh! Disgusting.
That's all I'm saying.

19:35.674 --> 19:36.575
Did you make love to him?

19:42.014 --> 19:43.382
Vlad: I owe you
an apology.

19:43.382 --> 19:45.518
Oh! Dude!

19:45.518 --> 19:47.253
You scared me.

19:47.253 --> 19:50.056
Yeah, well,
I scared myself.

19:50.056 --> 19:52.792
Very unlike me.

19:52.792 --> 19:54.393
I fell for your ex-wife.

19:54.393 --> 19:55.761
She told you?

19:55.761 --> 19:57.596
She mentioned
something, yeah.

19:57.596 --> 19:59.298
Well, she just
broke it off.

19:59.298 --> 20:01.100
Me working for you,
her working with me.

20:01.100 --> 20:03.636
The whole thing.

20:03.636 --> 20:06.472
Women...
Yeah. Women.

20:08.107 --> 20:10.276
Do you, uh...

20:10.276 --> 20:13.279
Do you think you can
put in a good word for me?

20:13.279 --> 20:14.480
That's a weird ask.

20:14.480 --> 20:15.948
I'll give you
this necklace in return.

20:15.948 --> 20:18.384
No, uh...
Vlad, that's really...

20:20.386 --> 20:23.289
Whoa! That is badass.

20:23.289 --> 20:25.791
I mean, is the chain
the snake?
Yep.

20:25.791 --> 20:27.560
Why is this thing
not on me right now?

20:27.560 --> 20:29.495
Huh? [ Chuckles ]

20:33.999 --> 20:36.469
Nope, it's too weird.

20:36.469 --> 20:38.270
Sorry.

20:38.270 --> 20:40.606
Well...

20:40.606 --> 20:43.008
I gave it
my best necklace.

20:43.008 --> 20:44.443
I don't know
what else I can do.

20:44.443 --> 20:47.613
Nothing, Vlad, there's
nothing you can do. Okay?

20:47.613 --> 20:49.815
And trust me,
it's a good thing.

20:49.815 --> 20:53.452
I mean, l-l-look at me,
sucked in, can't get out.

20:53.452 --> 20:54.520
Firmly under her thumb.

20:54.520 --> 20:56.155
And yet you are smiling.

20:56.155 --> 20:59.825
[ Scoffs ] It's like
Stockholm Syndrome.

20:59.825 --> 21:00.860
I hate Stockholm.

21:00.860 --> 21:02.328
Exactly.

21:02.328 --> 21:03.929
Be free.

21:03.929 --> 21:06.699
Go live your life, man.

21:06.699 --> 21:14.707
♪♪

21:14.707 --> 21:17.176
50 bucks for the necklace?

21:17.176 --> 21:19.178
Okay don't move,
I'm gonna get my wallet.

21:19.178 --> 21:22.715
♪♪
